title._content: Rändrahnudega rannik / Coast with erratic boulders

description._content: Rändrahnudega rannik. Käsmu poolsaarel asub Eesti suurim kivikülv, mis on suuremalt jaolt kaunilt metsa sisse peidetud. Rahnud on jäänuk mandriliustiku taganemisest viimasel jääajal u 10.000 aasta eest. - - - Coast with erratic boulders. The peninsula of Käsmu has the largest field of boulders in Estonia, most of it beautifully hidden in the woods. The boulders were left here by the retreating glacial ice during the last major ice age some 10.000 years ago. ca 1900 Viitekood / Reference code: EAA.1451.1.109.3.11 Kirje andmebaasis FOTIS / Description in the database FOTIS: www.ra.ee/fotis/index.php?type=2&id=9529
